cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.RO, cs.SY. 

The paper discusses the extension of a model of artificial intelligence, projective simulation, to include meta-learning in reinforcement learning settings. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves learning and adaptation, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of reinforcement learning and the focus on adjusting learning parameters suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
